      "content": "Here's a revised internal monologue: \"As I walk through the city, I'm mindful of the way people stare at me when I speak, their eyes reading the tiny mistake in my pronunciation or the soft accent that's just 'foreign'. They treat me different from them, too - the white person behind the counter gives me a fawning smile, knows all the 'scientic' slang, but the Latino cashier barely acknowledges me, her expression tired and rehearsed. Even the quiet reverence I showed to the saints of my childhood here feels mocking - I'd kneel to thank God for the trials, but she just rolls her eyes. What would my abuela think of this place, where people obsess over their morning coffee and the ritual of shrugging and smiling instead of speaking truth?\"",
